      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "I thought modern jvm compilers would use escape analysis and stack allocation optimization on these objects. It&#39;d figure out the intermediate objects are method scoped and don&#39;t escape the method, then flatten the object fields onto the stack, then use traditional optimization to reduce the code to a single constructor call, passing in the live values to the new object that escapes.  Meaning, it would produce code as efficient as you can hand craft natively."
